            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Yes. Signaling a geographic region in ERAS indicates a strong preference, but it does not prevent you from applying to programs outside that region. Programs outside your signaled region will still receive your application, though they may prioritize applicants who signaled their specific region. If you have a strong reason to apply widely, go ahead, but focus your extra applications on historically IMG-friendly programs."
